        "## 1. My lane as an ML task (type)\n",
        "\n",
        "*Classification, clustering, ranking, or scoring — which one, and why?*"
      ],
      "id": "AOXvWpPZBAnu"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I am framing this as a Classification and Scoring task. We want to predict a binary label for each page: 1 (High Potential / Worth Refreshing) or 0 (Low Potential / Leave Alone). Along with the classification, generating a probability score between $0.0$ and $1.0$ allows us to rank the final recommendations, so content managers can easily prioritize the highest-scoring pages first."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vFhAeiKJBKmU"
