      "source": [
        "## 3. Success metric\n",
        "\n",
        "*One metric you can defend. What number means 'good'?*"
      ],
      "id": "SPmiW0S2BAny"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The Metric: Precision @ K (specifically Precision@50).\n",
        "\n",
        "What number means 'good': A precision score above 75% in our top 50 recommendations is our target for success. Because content budgets are tight, we care deeply about minimizing False Positives—we cannot afford to tell a writer to spend hours rewriting a page that yields zero business value. Every recommended page must count."
