      "source": [
        "## 5. Why ML beats a fixed rule here\n",
        "\n",
        "*What makes the pattern too messy for an if-statement?*"
      ],
      "id": "CTWLMkGGBAn1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "While humans can easily write a simple rule like \"Refresh pages older than 180 days,\" real search intent patterns are far too messy for fixed if/else statements. A page's success depends on non-linear interactions: a high-volume keyword might be heavily decayed, while a lower-volume keyword on an older page might be perfectly poised to reclaim traffic. A machine learning model (like a Decision Tree or Random Forest) can automatically map out these complex combinations across dozens of signals simultaneously, optimizing our Precision far better than any hand-crafted heuristic."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Y87O2D_qBdum"
